headline: KEYCORP AND SCOTIABANK COMPLETE STRATEGIC MINORITY INVESTMENT
summary: KeyCorp (NYSE: KEY) today announced that The Bank of Nova Scotia ("Scotiabank") has completed its purchase of KeyCorp's common stock with an investment of approximately $2.0 billion, as expected. With this investment, Scotiabank (TSX: BNS) (NYSE: BNS) now owns approximately 14.9% of KeyCorp's common stock. The parties received Federal Reserve approval for the transaction on December 12, 2024.
